<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920106-0066</DOCNO><DOCID>920106-0066.</DOCID><HL>   Sterling Optical Hearing   Is Continued Until Today</HL><DATE>01/06/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AMVC EYE</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)MEDICAL SUPPLIES, EYEGLASS MANUFACTURERS (MDS)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BANKRUPTCY DECLARATIONS AND PROCEEDINGS (BCY)STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)</GV><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Sterling Optical Corp. said a federalbankruptcy court continued until today a hearing on theeyewear company's application for secureddebtor-in-possession financing.   Sterling Optical last week filed for protection fromcreditors under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code inManhattan.</LP><TEXT>   The company at that time said it had agreed, subject tocourt approval, to sell certain properties to American VisionCenters Inc., an eyewear company.   Sterling said that because results of the hearing areuncertain, it had requested the New York Stock Exchange tocontinue the suspension of trading in its stock.   Other potential buyers have indicated interest in biddingfor some of Sterling's stores.   The company blamed its filing on poor sales and the burdenof financing debt.</TEXT></DOC>